"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Engineered for Performance<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-986fa25 animated-slow elementor-invisible elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"986fa25\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_animation&quot;:&quot;fadeInUp&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Leader Gate Valve<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-d8e3815 elementor-widget__width-initial elementor-widget-mobile__width-inherit elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"d8e3815\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-md-8\"><p>Gate valves typically feature a gate (wedge) that is raised and lowered by a threaded stem (rising stem design) to control the flow of fluid. The gate moves perpendicular to the direction of flow, providing a tight seal when closed.Gate valves are available in various materials such as cast iron, ductile iron, carbon steel, stainless steel, bronze, and other alloys. The choice of material depends on factors such as the type of fluid, temperature, pressure, and corrosion resistance requirements.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><\/div>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-80112af e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"80112af\" data-element_type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-32caf03 elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"32caf03\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div cla