\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Leader Globe Valves<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8fe21b1 elementor-widget__width-initial elementor-widget-mobile__width-inherit elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"8fe21b1\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-md-8\"><p>Globe valves have a globe-shaped body with an internal baffle and a movable disk or plug that seats against the valve seat to regulate the flow of fluid. The disk is connected to a stem that moves up and down to control the flow, hence the name &#8220;globe&#8221; valve.Globe valves are available in various materials to suit different operating conditions and fluid types. Common materials include carbon steel, stainless steel, cast iron, bronze, and other alloys.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><\/div>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-b4a1939 e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"b4a1939\" data-element_type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-6fccbca elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"6fccbca\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" width=\"500\" height=\"290\" src=\"https:\/\/Navjivanvalves.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/leader-globe-valves.jpg\" class=\"attachment-large size-large wp-image-2803\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/Navjivanvalves.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/leader-globe-valves.jpg 500w, https:\/\/Navjivanvalves.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/leader-globe-valves-300x174.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-3d4d911 e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent\" data-id=\"3d4d911\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-09eae8f e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"09eae8f\" data-element_type=\"container\">\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8827c77 e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"8827c77\" data-element_type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-bd02367 animated-slow elementor-invisible elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"bd02367\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_animation&quot;:&quot;fadeInUp&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Engineered for Performance<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-d7e17fc animated-slow elementor-invisible elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"d7e17fc\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_animation&quot;:&quot;fadeInUp&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Leader Check Valves<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-4332205 elementor-widget__width-initial elementor-widget-mobile__width-inherit elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"4332205\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-md-8\"><p>Check valves, also known as non-return valves or one-way valves, have a simple design that allows flow in one direction while preventing reverse flow. Leader Check Valves typically consist of a body with an inlet and outlet port, a movable disc or poppet, and a mechanism such as a spring or gravity that keeps the disc closed when there is no forward flow. Check valves are available in various materials to suit different applications and operating conditions. Common materials include carbon steel, stainless steel, cast iron, bronze, and other alloys.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><\/div>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-e24a62e e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"e24a62e\" data-element_type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-0702bb4 elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"0702bb4\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" width=\"500\" height=\"290\" src=\"https:\/\/Navjivanvalves.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/leader-check-valves.jpg\" class=\"attachment-large size-large wp-image-2804\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/Navjivanvalves.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/leader-check-valves.jpg 500w, https:\/\/Navjivanvalves.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/04\/leader-check-valves-300x174.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c141684 e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent\" data-id=\"c141684\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-3184143 e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"3184143\" data-element_type=\"container\">\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-10ea2dc e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"10ea2dc\" data-element_type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-5427e2e animated-slow elementor-invisible elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"5427e2e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_animation&quot;:&quot;fadeInUp&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Engineered for Performance<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-de81e53 animated-slow elementor-invisible elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"de81e53\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_animation&quot;:&quot;fadeInUp&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Leader Forged Steel valves<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-37de537 elementor-widget__width-initial elementor-widget-mobile__width-inherit elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"37de537\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Forged Steel Valves<\/strong> are valves whose components, particularly the body and bonnet, are manufactured using the forging process. This process involves shaping metal under high pressure and high temperatures to improve the strength and integrity of the material. Forged Steel Valves are known for their robustness and durability. Forged Steel Valves are typically made from forged carbon steel, forged stainless steel, or other forged alloys. These material